title: The Squiddening
author: Krystanburge
pages:
#- Jimmy seemed scared.
The giant squid had tracked him down; down right to his very home.
"Wh-what do you want..?" said Jimmy. "I... want to feast... on your soul..." Said the giant squid, ominously. This sentiment struck fear into Jimmy's very soul, as it 
#- were. Jimmy broke through his hastily built back wall with his fists. He didn't care that his fists were bloodied, nor that he would be leaving behind his very home, all he desired to do was run. Run from the voice. The squid stood humbly awaiting his 
#- reply, unaware of his escape. Suddenly, the squid broke through his door to find an empty house. "Where... where are you..." The squid muttered under his breath. Jimmy was far, far away as of the moment, however. The squid flopped and flailed in anger at 
#- its' misfortune. He did notice something, though: The broken wall, and a path of shakily produced footprints leading off into the snow...
#- 